originContent: A web interface for Stable Diffusion, implemented using Gradio library.
translatedContent: A web interface for Stable Diffusion, implemented using Gradio library.

originContent: - One click install and run script (but you still must install python and git)
translatedContent: - One click install and run script (but you still must install python and git)

originContent: - Attention, specify parts of text that the model should pay more attention to
translatedContent: - Attention, specify parts of text that the model should pay more attention to

originContent: - a man in a `((tuxedo))` - will pay more attention to tuxedo
translatedContent: - a man in a `((tuxedo))` - will pay more attention to tuxedo

originContent: - a man in a `(tuxedo:1.21)` - alternative syntax
translatedContent: - a man in a `(tuxedo:1.21)` - alternative syntax

originContent: - select text and press `Ctrl+Up` or `Ctrl+Down` (or `Command+Up` or `Command+Down` if you're on a MacOS) to automatically adjust attention to selected text (code contributed by anonymous user)
translatedContent: - select text and press `Ctrl+Up` or `Ctrl+Down` (or `Command+Up` or `Command+Down` if you're on a MacOS) to automatically adjust attention to selected text (code contributed by anonymous user)

originContent: - Loopback, run img2img processing multiple times
translatedContent: - Loopback, run img2img processing multiple times

originContent: - X/Y/Z plot, a way to draw a 3 dimensional plot of images with different parameters
translatedContent: - X/Y/Z plot, a way to draw a 3 dimensional plot of images with different parameters

originContent: - have as many embeddings as you want and use any names you like for them
translatedContent: - have as many embeddings as you want and use any names you like for them

originContent: - use multiple embeddings with different numbers of vectors per token
translatedContent: - use multiple embeddings with different numbers of vectors per token

originContent: - works with half precision floating point numbers
translatedContent: - works with half precision floating point numbers

originContent: - train embeddings on 8GB (also reports of 6GB working)
translatedContent: - train embeddings on 8GB (also reports of 6GB working)

originContent: - GFPGAN, neural network that fixes faces
translatedContent: - GFPGAN, neural network that fixes faces

originContent: - CodeFormer, face restoration tool as an alternative to GFPGAN
translatedContent: - CodeFormer, face restoration tool as an alternative to GFPGAN

originContent: - ESRGAN, neural network upscaler with a lot of third party models
translatedContent: - ESRGAN, neural network upscaler with a lot of third party models

originContent: - SwinIR and Swin2SR ([see here](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/pull/2092)), neural network upscalers
translatedContent: - SwinIR and Swin2SR ([see here](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/pull/2092)), neural network upscalers

originContent: - LDSR, Latent diffusion super resolution upscaling
translatedContent: - LDSR, Latent diffusion super resolution upscaling

originContent: - 4GB video card support (also reports of 2GB working)
translatedContent: - 4GB video card support (also reports of 2GB working)

originContent: - parameters you used to generate images are saved with that image
translatedContent: - parameters you used to generate images are saved with that image

originContent: - in PNG chunks for PNG, in EXIF for JPEG
translatedContent: - in PNG chunks for PNG, in EXIF for JPEG

originContent: - can drag the image to PNG info tab to restore generation parameters and automatically copy them into UI
translatedContent: - can drag the image to PNG info tab to restore generation parameters and automatically copy them into UI

originContent: - drag and drop an image/text-parameters to promptbox
translatedContent: - drag and drop an image/text-parameters to promptbox

originContent: - Read Generation Parameters Button, loads parameters in promptbox to UI
translatedContent: - Read Generation Parameters Button, loads parameters in promptbox to UI

originContent: - Running arbitrary python code from UI (must run with `--allow-code` to enable)
translatedContent: - Running arbitrary python code from UI (must run with `--allow-code` to enable)

originContent: - Mouseover hints for most UI elements
translatedContent: - Mouseover hints for most UI elements

originContent: - Possible to change defaults/mix/max/step values for UI elements via text config
translatedContent: - Possible to change defaults/mix/max/step values for UI elements via text config

originContent: - Tiling support, a checkbox to create images that can be tiled like textures
translatedContent: - Tiling support, a checkbox to create images that can be tiled like textures

originContent: - Progress bar and live image generation preview
translatedContent: - Progress bar and live image generation preview

originContent: - Can use a separate neural network to produce previews with almost none VRAM or compute requirement
translatedContent: - Can use a separate neural network to produce previews with almost none VRAM or compute requirement

originContent: - Negative prompt, an extra text field that allows you to list what you don't want to see in generated image
translatedContent: - Negative prompt, an extra text field that allows you to list what you don't want to see in generated image

originContent: - Styles, a way to save part of prompt and easily apply them via dropdown later
translatedContent: - Styles, a way to save part of prompt and easily apply them via dropdown later

originContent: - Variations, a way to generate same image but with tiny differences
translatedContent: - Variations, a way to generate same image but with tiny differences

originContent: - Seed resizing, a way to generate same image but at slightly different resolution
translatedContent: - Seed resizing, a way to generate same image but at slightly different resolution

originContent: - CLIP interrogator, a button that tries to guess prompt from an image
translatedContent: - CLIP interrogator, a button that tries to guess prompt from an image

originContent: - Prompt Editing, a way to change prompt mid-generation, say to start making a watermelon and switch to anime girl midway
translatedContent: - Prompt Editing, a way to change prompt mid-generation, say to start making a watermelon and switch to anime girl midway

originContent: - Batch Processing, process a group of files using img2img
translatedContent: - Batch Processing, process a group of files using img2img

originContent: - Img2img Alternative, reverse Euler method of cross attention control
translatedContent: - Img2img Alternative, reverse Euler method of cross attention control

originContent: - Highres Fix, a convenience option to produce high resolution pictures in one click without usual distortions
translatedContent: - Highres Fix, a convenience option to produce high resolution pictures in one click without usual distortions

originContent: - Checkpoint Merger, a tab that allows you to merge up to 3 checkpoints into one
translatedContent: - Checkpoint Merger, a tab that allows you to merge up to 3 checkpoints into one

originContent: - [Composable-Diffusion](https://energy-based-model.github.io/Compositional-Visual-Generation-with-Composable-Diffusion-Models/), a way to use multiple prompts at once
translatedContent: - [Composable-Diffusion](https://energy-based-model.github.io/Compositional-Visual-Generation-with-Composable-Diffusion-Models/), a way to use multiple prompts at once

originContent: - also supports weights for prompts: `a cat :1.2 AND a dog AND a penguin :2.2`
translatedContent: - also supports weights for prompts: `a cat :1.2 AND a dog AND a penguin :2.2`

originContent: - No token limit for prompts (original stable diffusion lets you use up to 75 tokens)
translatedContent: - No token limit for prompts (original stable diffusion lets you use up to 75 tokens)

originContent: - DeepDanbooru integration, creates danbooru style tags for anime prompts
translatedContent: - DeepDanbooru integration, creates danbooru style tags for anime prompts

originContent: - [xformers](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/wiki/Xformers), major speed increase for select cards: (add `--xformers` to commandline args)
translatedContent: - [xformers](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/wiki/Xformers), major speed increase for select cards: (add `--xformers` to commandline args)

originContent: - via extension: [History tab](https://github.com/yfszzx/stable-diffusion-webui-images-browser): view, direct and delete images conveniently within the UI
translatedContent: - via extension: [History tab](https://github.com/yfszzx/stable-diffusion-webui-images-browser): view, direct and delete images conveniently within the UI

originContent: - Preprocessing images: cropping, mirroring, autotagging using BLIP or deepdanbooru (for anime)
translatedContent: - Preprocessing images: cropping, mirroring, autotagging using BLIP or deepdanbooru (for anime)

originContent: - Loras (same as Hypernetworks but more pretty)
translatedContent: - Loras (same as Hypernetworks but more pretty)

originContent: - A separate UI where you can choose, with preview, which embeddings, hypernetworks or Loras to add to your prompt
translatedContent: - A separate UI where you can choose, with preview, which embeddings, hypernetworks or Loras to add to your prompt

originContent: - Can select to load a different VAE from settings screen
translatedContent: - Can select to load a different VAE from settings screen

originContent: - Estimated completion time in progress bar
translatedContent: - Estimated completion time in progress bar

originContent: - via extension: [Aesthetic Gradients](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui-aesthetic-gradients), a way to generate images with a specific aesthetic by using clip images embeds (implementation of [https://github.com/vicgalle/stable-diffusion-aesthetic-gradients](https://github.com/vicgalle/stable-diffusion-aesthetic-gradients))
translatedContent: - via extension: [Aesthetic Gradients](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui-aesthetic-gradients), a way to generate images with a specific aesthetic by using clip images embeds (implementation of [https://github.com/vicgalle/stable-diffusion-aesthetic-gradients](https://github.com/vicgalle/stable-diffusion-aesthetic-gradients))

originContent: - Eased resolution restriction: generated image's dimensions must be a multiple of 8 rather than 64
translatedContent: - Eased resolution restriction: generated image's dimensions must be a multiple of 8 rather than 64

originContent: - Reorder elements in the UI from settings screen
translatedContent: - Reorder elements in the UI from settings screen

originContent: ### Installation on Windows 10/11 with NVidia-GPUs using release package
translatedContent: ### Installation on Windows 10/11 with NVidia-GPUs using release package

originContent: 1. Download `sd.webui.zip` from [v1.0.0-pre](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/releases/tag/v1.0.0-pre) and extract its contents.
translatedContent: 1. Download `sd.webui.zip` from [v1.0.0-pre](https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui/releases/tag/v1.0.0-pre) and extract its contents.

originContent: 1. Install [Python 3.10.6](https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3106/) (Newer version of Python does not support torch), checking "Add Python to PATH".
translatedContent: 1. Install [Python 3.10.6](https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3106/) (Newer version of Python does not support torch), checking "Add Python to PATH".

originContent: 3. Download the stable-diffusion-webui repository, for example by running `git clone https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui.git`.
translatedContent: 3. Download the stable-diffusion-webui repository, for example by running `git clone https://github.com/AUTOMATIC1111/stable-diffusion-webui.git`.

originContent: 4. Run `webui-user.bat` from Windows Explorer as normal, non-administrator, user.
translatedContent: 4. Run `webui-user.bat` from Windows Explorer as normal, non-administrator, user.

originContent: sudo apt install wget git python3 python3-venv libgl1 libglib2.0-0
translatedContent: sudo apt install wget git python3 python3-venv libgl1 libglib2.0-0

originContent: sudo dnf install wget git python3 gperftools-libs libglvnd-glx
translatedContent: sudo dnf install wget git python3 gperftools-libs libglvnd-glx

originContent: sudo zypper install wget git python3 libtcmalloc4 libglvnd
translatedContent: sudo zypper install wget git python3 libtcmalloc4 libglvnd

originContent: If your system is very new, you need to install python3.11 or python3.10:
translatedContent: If your system is very new, you need to install python3.11 or python3.10:

originContent: yay -S python311 # do not confuse with python3.11 package
translatedContent: yay -S python311 # do not confuse with python3.11 package

originContent: # Then set up env variable in launch script
translatedContent: # Then set up env variable in launch script
